ary\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Identifying potential compile issues**\\\\n\\\\nI'm noticing a possible compile issue with the `ClassLoader.getResourceAsStream` method; it returns an InputStream and doesn't throw exceptions. Then there's `ClientBuilder`, which implements `Configurable<ClientBuilder>`, but I'm wondering if the methods have the correct types from the generic `Configurable<ClientBuilder>` in the API. Oh, and should `BaseClientBuilder` be private with a public nested subclass extending the private superclass? I'm pondering if that's allowed.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Implemented focused coverage for `javax.ws.rs.client.FactoryFinder`.\\n\\nChanged files:\\n- `tests/src/javax.ws.rs/javax.ws.rs-api/2.0.1/src/test/java/javax_ws_rs/javax_ws_rs_api/FactoryFinderTest.java`\\n  - Added tests exercising:\\n    - context classloader service lookup\\n    - system service lookup when TCCL is `null`\\n    - fallback from custom classloader `Class.forName(..., classLoader)` to current loader `Class.forName(...)`\\n    - provider instantiation through `Class#newInstance()`\\n- `tests/src/javax.ws.rs/javax.ws.rs-api/2.0.1/src/test/resources/META-INF/services/javax.ws.rs.client.ClientBuilder`\\n  - Added service descriptor for the test `ClientBuilder` provider.\\n- `tests/src/javax.ws.rs/javax.ws.rs-api/2.0.1/src/test/java/javax_ws_rs/javax_ws_rs_api/Javax_ws_rs_apiTest.java`\\n  - Made the existing top-level test class `public` per repository rules.\\n\\nI did not run or compile the tests, per instructions.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0dfd86d8e75194920169f693ae3e90819c8b2c2720c63e2f40\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 431, \"output\": 1122, \"cacheRead\": 30720, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 32273, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"